<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/393116-democracy-will-never-be-supplanted-by-a">“Democracy will never be supplanted by a republic of experts—and that is a very good thing.” Why is it a good thing?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_393116'><a id="like_count_community_question_393116" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/393116?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">4 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F18736925-capital-in-the-twenty-first-century">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/393116-democracy-will-never-be-supplanted-by-a">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/393116-democracy-will-never-be-supplanted-by-a">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6213795-julien-v"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1533655945i/6213795._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6213795-julien-v">Julien V</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Because democracy allows every adult to express their ideas and interests. It is a political right, and a good thing *in itself*. <br/><br/>Experts are needed, <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Because democracy allows every adult to express their ideas and interests. It is a political right, and a good thing *in itself*. <br /><br />Experts are needed, because not everyone has the time, knowledge or capacity to process the complex data behind every economic policy. But experts in a particular field may have particular interests and thus misinterpret or misrepresent the majority's well-being. <br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
